1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,433
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,433 --> 00:00:02,800
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,333 --> 00:00:06,500
The will must be somewhere around here.

4
00:00:07,700 --> 00:00:08,700
What is this?

5
00:00:25,277 --> 00:00:27,547
Why is this cheap necklace...

6
00:00:28,328 --> 00:00:31,776
wrapped up so carefully?

7
00:00:34,475 --> 00:00:35,475
Su Jeong!

8
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:37,408
Mother.

9
00:00:42,168 --> 00:00:44,368
Mother, what's wrong?

10
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:45,933
What is that?

11
00:00:46,120 --> 00:00:47,120
Whatever it is,

12
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:50,400
why are you going through my things
without permission?

13
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:53,133
Well, I just thought,
since you were both out,

14
00:00:53,504 --> 00:00:55,200
I'd do a bit of cleaning.

15
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:56,233
Cleaning?

16
00:00:57,085 --> 00:00:59,112
Since when do you clean our room?

17
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:04,533
What's going on?
What's with all the noise?

18
00:01:06,264 --> 00:01:07,300
It's nothing.

19
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Nothing at all.

20
00:01:11,523 --> 00:01:13,100
- You should leave.
- Sorry?

21
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:16,700
Yes. Please rest, Mother.

22
00:01:22,733 --> 00:01:23,763
Why?

23
00:01:24,433 --> 00:01:26,752
Did Su Jeong do something wrong?

24
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:28,333
Not really.

25
00:01:29,033 --> 00:01:30,900
She just went into a room
that wasn't hers.

26
00:01:32,115 --> 00:01:34,133
Shall I run a bath for you?

27
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:36,700
No, I'll do it myself.

28
00:01:52,312 --> 00:01:53,312
That startled me.

29
00:01:54,216 --> 00:01:56,300
She's got quite a temper.

30
00:01:57,947 --> 00:01:59,147
But what was that necklace?

31
00:02:00,075 --> 00:02:01,563
Why did she react so strongly?

32
00:02:03,823 --> 00:02:06,223
I smell something fishy.

33
00:02:07,763 --> 00:02:08,763
What? 200,000 dollars?

34
00:02:09,844 --> 00:02:12,244
What kind of condition is that?

35
00:02:13,512 --> 00:02:15,280
I'm just as shocked,

36
00:02:16,901 --> 00:02:18,533
but this kind of opportunity
won't come again.

37
00:02:19,557 --> 00:02:21,900
Philosophy departments are shutting down,

38
00:02:22,669 --> 00:02:25,144
and even lecturer positions
are disappearing.

39
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,656
I really want to find a way
to get that money...

40
00:02:29,464 --> 00:02:31,400
and make him seize this chance, Mother.

41
00:02:31,533 --> 00:02:34,451
Of course he should take it.

42
00:02:34,933 --> 00:02:36,397
So...

43
00:02:36,979 --> 00:02:38,679
I've already canceled
Bit Na's education insurance...

44
00:02:38,679 --> 00:02:41,136
and the housing savings plan,

45
00:02:41,653 --> 00:02:43,680
and I'm trying to gather money
from everywhere.

46
00:02:44,147 --> 00:02:45,405
But the problem is Eun Hyeong.

47
00:02:45,405 --> 00:02:46,413
Why him?

48
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:49,875
He says he can't buy a professorship
with money,

49
00:02:50,667 --> 00:02:53,147
talking about his conscience and pride
as a scholar.

50
00:02:53,381 --> 00:02:57,275
That does sound like
something he would say.

51
00:02:57,533 --> 00:03:01,573
All this time, I've neglected
the house and Bit Na,

52
00:03:02,233 --> 00:03:04,725
been treated like someone
who only cares about work,

53
00:03:05,936 --> 00:03:07,000
but I lived for just one thing,

54
00:03:07,736 --> 00:03:09,600
Eun Hyeong's future, Mother.

55
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:11,700
I know.

56
00:03:12,269 --> 00:03:14,100
Of course I know how you've lived...

57
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,800
and how you feel.

58
00:03:16,365 --> 00:03:17,500
But now,

59
00:03:17,984 --> 00:03:20,100
he's saying he'll throw away
this hard-earned opportunity...

60
00:03:20,368 --> 00:03:23,300
for the sake of his conscience and pride.

61
00:03:23,979 --> 00:03:26,933
I honestly don't know
how to go on with him.

62
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,400
Don't worry, Ji Seon.

63
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:34,900
That money...

64
00:03:36,033 --> 00:03:37,133
I'll get it.

65
00:03:39,633 --> 00:03:41,900
How could you possibly raise that much?

66
00:03:43,037 --> 00:03:45,100
We'll look into loans
at my husband's company...

67
00:03:45,957 --> 00:03:49,233
and break the savings we set aside
for retirement.

68
00:03:49,872 --> 00:03:51,000
And if needed,

69
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:53,633
we'll use my husband's severance pay.

70
00:03:54,133 --> 00:03:56,100
It's my son's future at stake.

71
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:58,000
I'll make it happen somehow.

72
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:00,700
Even if we get the money,

73
00:04:01,163 --> 00:04:02,800
what if he still refuses?

74
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,100
I'll convince him no matter what.

75
00:04:05,563 --> 00:04:07,500
Don't worry. Just trust me, okay?

76
00:04:08,664 --> 00:04:10,100
Mother.

77
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,100
(Kangsu Construction)

78
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:22,400
That beer mix from last night
must've been strong.

79
00:04:22,896 --> 00:04:24,100
Are you feeling okay?

80
00:04:24,339 --> 00:04:25,800
I didn't drink much.

81
00:04:28,243 --> 00:04:29,600
- Would you like one?
- What?

82
00:04:30,299 --> 00:04:31,400
Sure, thanks.

83
00:04:39,037 --> 00:04:40,400
I feel better.

84
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,685
Weren't you going to give that...

85
00:04:46,685 --> 00:04:48,400
to Team Manager Ko this morning?

86
00:04:50,843 --> 00:04:52,533
She was about to give it to him,

87
00:04:52,533 --> 00:04:56,333
but Ms. Cho Eun Ae already put
the hangover jelly into his mouth...

88
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:58,400
Let's stop chatting and start the meeting.

89
00:05:01,955 --> 00:05:02,955
Let's begin.

90
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:25,833
(U.S. Young Architect of the Year Award,
awarded to Korean architect Ko Gyeol)

91
00:05:28,266 --> 00:05:29,500
(His work focuses on shaping ways of life
and relationships, not flashy design.)

92
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:31,433
Well, well.

93
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:34,949
His philosophy and personality
are completely different.

94
00:05:35,613 --> 00:05:38,400
How can someone who designs
with such warmth and openness...

95
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,200
be so prickly in real life?

96
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:47,000
My grandfather,

97
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,200
who stood by me when I was all alone...

98
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:52,700
and helped me get to where I am today.

99
00:05:53,661 --> 00:05:55,400
Grandfather?

100
00:05:56,715 --> 00:05:58,300
The chairman of Kangsu Group?

101
00:06:00,659 --> 00:06:02,800
So he's a real silver spoon, isn't he?

102
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:04,848
So annoying.

103
00:06:05,987 --> 00:06:07,500
There you are.

104
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:10,600
I thought you left early
from overdoing it yesterday.

105
00:06:10,981 --> 00:06:12,433
An intern leaving early? No way.

106
00:06:13,971 --> 00:06:16,900
What was that song you sang
with the team manager yesterday?

107
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:19,933
What? I sang with him?

108
00:06:20,909 --> 00:06:22,833
Looks like you blacked out completely.

109
00:06:23,229 --> 00:06:25,133
He was singing,

110
00:06:25,133 --> 00:06:27,800
and you suddenly jumped up and joined him.

111
00:06:28,269 --> 00:06:30,133
I thought you were forming a duet.

112
00:06:32,389 --> 00:06:39,277
- <i>On hungry days</i>
- <i>On hungry days</i>

113
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:43,366
We need to go for a third round!

114
00:06:43,366 --> 00:06:45,100
- There's no third round. Just get in.
- A third round!

115
00:06:47,100 --> 00:06:49,033
This way? That way?

116
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:50,033
It should be around here.

117
00:06:50,033 --> 00:06:51,600
- Go inside.
- What? Go where?

118
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:52,909
What do you mean, three rounds?

119
00:06:53,069 --> 00:06:55,453
I found these earmuffs in my pocket.

120
00:06:56,157 --> 00:06:58,216
His name is Ko Gyeol,
which sounds like noble.

121
00:06:58,469 --> 00:06:59,533
Noble, my foot.

122
00:06:59,533 --> 00:07:01,700
If you're noble, I'm a good girl.

123
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:02,700
Good girl.

124
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,147
I need to go home and check!

125
00:07:05,221 --> 00:07:07,312
Team Manager, hold my stomach.

126
00:07:07,312 --> 00:07:08,517
What's wrong with you?

127
00:07:08,851 --> 00:07:11,093
This is nuts. What do I do?

128
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:13,500
Why? People black out sometimes.

129
00:07:14,029 --> 00:07:17,000
Still,
the dinner was really fun thanks to you.

130
00:07:18,475 --> 00:07:20,900
Want me to send you the duet video?

131
00:07:21,100 --> 00:07:22,500
What? A video?

132
00:07:22,672 --> 00:07:24,733
No! Delete it right now!

133
00:07:24,733 --> 00:07:26,400
I already sent it to him.

134
00:07:27,315 --> 00:07:28,317
He hasn't checked it yet.

135
00:07:30,145 --> 00:07:32,405
Delete!

136
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:35,833
It's probably too late to delete it now.

137
00:07:43,797 --> 00:07:46,500
A necklace? What necklace?

138
00:07:46,811 --> 00:07:48,557
It wasn't even something expensive,

139
00:07:48,557 --> 00:07:50,149
just a cheap-looking thing,

140
00:07:50,392 --> 00:07:52,333
but she had it hidden deep in a drawer.

141
00:07:53,459 --> 00:07:55,233
And she got so angry over it.

142
00:07:56,317 --> 00:07:58,600
I thought my heart was going to stop.

143
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:02,000
Why were you even going
through their room?

144
00:08:02,325 --> 00:08:04,800
What if Father had caught you?

145
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:07,653
I mean, he's always calling in Mr. Seo,

146
00:08:07,933 --> 00:08:09,633
and the three of them keep whispering,

147
00:08:10,277 --> 00:08:12,333
so I figured
it had something to do with the will...

148
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:14,600
and went in to check.

149
00:08:16,233 --> 00:08:18,600
But the thing is,

150
00:08:18,989 --> 00:08:21,033
it seemed like Father didn't know
about that necklace.

151
00:08:22,033 --> 00:08:23,233
What do you mean?

152
00:08:23,233 --> 00:08:26,433
She hid it quickly when he came in.

153
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:31,100
There must be some big secret...

154
00:08:31,233 --> 00:08:32,900
Father doesn't know about.

155
00:08:34,033 --> 00:08:35,300
That doesn't sound like her.

156
00:08:35,448 --> 00:08:37,600
Does it say that on her forehead?

157
00:08:39,371 --> 00:08:41,000
Something feels off to me.

158
00:08:42,464 --> 00:08:45,333
So, what are you going to do now?

159
00:08:45,859 --> 00:08:48,500
If Father stays wrapped around her
like that,

160
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:51,267
you and Min Ho will end up with nothing.

161
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:53,867
What do you mean, nothing?

162
00:08:54,301 --> 00:08:56,400
Father's not that easy to manipulate.

163
00:08:57,139 --> 00:09:00,933
And Min Ho's been working so hard lately.

164
00:09:00,933 --> 00:09:04,200
He's really stepped up.

165
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,624
This time,

166
00:09:05,624 --> 00:09:07,333
Min Ho has to beat Gyeol...

167
00:09:07,715 --> 00:09:08,900
and prove himself to Father...

168
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:12,200
as the next chairman of Kangsu Group.

169
00:09:13,192 --> 00:09:15,833
Next? You mean the one after next.

170
00:09:16,976 --> 00:09:18,200
Right.

171
00:09:18,573 --> 00:09:20,957
The next one is my husband.

172
00:09:21,433 --> 00:09:22,433
Honey.

173
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:25,800
Come here.

174
00:09:26,701 --> 00:09:28,600
- I said come here.
- Where?

175
00:09:28,933 --> 00:09:30,500
The comforter... Come here.

176
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:31,800
Get this away.

177
00:09:33,033 --> 00:09:34,033
Come closer.

178
00:09:50,733 --> 00:09:55,700
- <i>On hungry days</i>
- <i>On hungry days</i>

179
00:09:56,133 --> 00:10:01,000
- <i>I quietly picked and ate them</i>
- <i>I quietly picked and ate them</i>

180
00:10:01,233 --> 00:10:02,283
Come in.

181
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:05,200
- <i>Calling "Mom, Mom"</i>
- <i>Calling "Mom, Mom"</i>

182
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:07,433
- Grandma.
- Hey, what were you doing?

183
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:11,261
We went to karaoke at a team dinner,

184
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:12,633
and someone sent me this.

185
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:16,200
That's good.
You seem to be adjusting well.

186
00:10:17,576 --> 00:10:18,600
Wait.

187
00:10:19,133 --> 00:10:21,200
If you sing that kind of song at karaoke,

188
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:23,600
people will say it ruins the mood
and won't like it.

189
00:10:24,283 --> 00:10:26,033
But it's my favorite song.

190
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:27,933
When I was little,

191
00:10:27,933 --> 00:10:29,475
whenever I had nightmares
and couldn't sleep,

192
00:10:29,648 --> 00:10:31,233
you always sang it for me.

193
00:10:31,928 --> 00:10:33,733
Do you still have nightmares these days?

194
00:10:34,131 --> 00:10:36,331
No, I'm better now.

195
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:37,800
That's good.

196
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:41,633
By the way, who did you sing it with?

197
00:10:42,672 --> 00:10:44,500
A new hire on the planning team.

198
00:10:46,024 --> 00:10:47,500
She's someone you know too.

199
00:10:47,933 --> 00:10:48,933
What?

200
00:10:49,109 --> 00:10:51,861
She's the one who installed the Joy app
on your phone...

201
00:10:51,861 --> 00:10:53,100
when you almost collapsed on the street.

202
00:10:55,051 --> 00:10:57,233
That girl's on your team now?

203
00:10:57,300 --> 00:11:00,133
Yes, our company bought Joy.

204
00:11:01,123 --> 00:11:03,533
She's the developer,
so we're working together.

205
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,800
That's great.

206
00:11:06,272 --> 00:11:07,900
She seemed like a good person.

207
00:11:09,107 --> 00:11:10,216
Yeah, well.

208
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:13,300
It's quince tea. Drink it.

209
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:14,557
Thank you.

210
00:11:14,557 --> 00:11:15,600
- Good night, Grandma.
- Good night.

211
00:11:26,107 --> 00:11:30,800
- <i>I quietly picked and ate them</i>
- <i>I quietly picked and ate them</i>

212
00:11:31,387 --> 00:11:33,488
Excuse me, Team Manager Ko Gyeol.

213
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:37,233
If you're noble, I'm a good girl.

214
00:11:37,651 --> 00:11:39,833
A very, very good girl.

215
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,333
Good girl.

216
00:11:42,864 --> 00:11:44,400
Good girl, my foot.

217
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:50,480
For 30 years, without missing a month,

218
00:11:51,365 --> 00:11:53,500
your salary has gone into this account.

219
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:56,733
Where did it all go?

220
00:11:58,433 --> 00:11:59,433
Goodness.

221
00:12:02,233 --> 00:12:05,233
Thanks to you, we've lived well,

222
00:12:06,048 --> 00:12:07,900
fed the kids, and educated them.

223
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,233
You've done so much.

224
00:12:10,747 --> 00:12:13,200
I'm going to cancel everything I can
for now.

225
00:12:14,033 --> 00:12:17,133
Let's take that Europe trip
when you turn 70.

226
00:12:18,100 --> 00:12:19,100
That's okay, right?

227
00:12:20,033 --> 00:12:22,400
Yeah, that's fine, but...

228
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:24,133
As soon as you get to work tomorrow,

229
00:12:24,533 --> 00:12:26,833
find out how much you can borrow.

230
00:12:27,333 --> 00:12:28,900
If they can't give you a loan,

231
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:31,600
see if you can access
your severance pay early.

232
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:32,900
Make sure you look into that too.

233
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:35,200
Severance pay?

234
00:12:35,515 --> 00:12:38,833
Why? Are you worried about using it early?

235
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:43,433
We'll manage somehow later.

236
00:12:44,533 --> 00:12:47,100
Once Eun Hyeong settles down,
I'll ask him to pay it back bit by bit.

237
00:12:47,328 --> 00:12:49,400
Don't you think the order is wrong?

238
00:12:50,104 --> 00:12:53,520
Eun Hyeong said he would never buy
a professorship with money,

239
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:55,200
and yet you're trying
to raise the money first?

240
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:58,100
Are you thinking the same as him?

241
00:12:58,677 --> 00:13:00,933
About scholarly pride and conscience?

242
00:13:01,368 --> 00:13:03,533
Yes, I am.

243
00:13:03,981 --> 00:13:06,600
And even if we got the money,

244
00:13:06,861 --> 00:13:08,433
do you think he'd accept it?

245
00:13:08,433 --> 00:13:11,533
Please think realistically.

246
00:13:11,900 --> 00:13:13,829
Bit Na starts elementary school next year.

247
00:13:13,829 --> 00:13:16,000
They'll have even more expenses ahead.

248
00:13:16,419 --> 00:13:17,600
If he loses this chance,

249
00:13:18,100 --> 00:13:21,059
he has to keep being a homemaker...

250
00:13:21,059 --> 00:13:22,359
with Ji Seon as the breadwinner.

251
00:13:24,233 --> 00:13:26,400
I can't watch Eun Hyeong collapse
like this.

252
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:28,433
What do you mean, collapse?

253
00:13:29,133 --> 00:13:31,600
Does his life end if he's not a professor?

254
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:33,300
That's not what I mean.

255
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:35,500
Look at yourself.

256
00:13:35,741 --> 00:13:39,000
You spent 30 years at a major company
and are now an executive.

257
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:41,633
Because you stood strong,

258
00:13:41,633 --> 00:13:44,300
our children grew up well.

259
00:13:44,533 --> 00:13:45,733
One has a doctorate, one is a doctor,

260
00:13:45,733 --> 00:13:47,633
and one is working at a big company.

261
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:51,168
How do you think Eun Hyeong feels,

262
00:13:51,168 --> 00:13:53,700
having grown up watching
a father like that?

263
00:13:53,933 --> 00:13:56,833
Don't you think he wants to be...

264
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:59,300
a good husband and father like you?

265
00:14:05,765 --> 00:14:08,600
No matter what, I'm going to make sure
he takes this opportunity.

266
00:14:09,037 --> 00:14:10,100
Got it?

267
00:14:14,859 --> 00:14:18,500
If only we had money
to support him easily.

268
00:14:19,928 --> 00:14:23,033
Cho Seong Jun, is Eun Hyeong's opinion
really that important?

269
00:14:24,152 --> 00:14:26,000
Or is it just that I can't get the money?

270
00:14:27,005 --> 00:14:28,633
How could we possibly raise that much?

271
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:36,464
Dad, why are you still up?

272
00:14:37,573 --> 00:14:39,500
I couldn't sleep.

273
00:14:39,805 --> 00:14:40,944
Why are you out?

274
00:14:40,944 --> 00:14:42,862
I'm going for a run.

275
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:44,400
At this hour?

276
00:14:44,611 --> 00:14:46,033
When I have too many thoughts,

277
00:14:46,033 --> 00:14:48,000
running without thinking helps.

278
00:14:48,565 --> 00:14:49,765
Want to join me?

279
00:14:50,633 --> 00:14:51,633
Sure.

280
00:15:08,307 --> 00:15:11,100
I'm too exhausted to run any further.

281
00:15:11,856 --> 00:15:12,900
Me too.

282
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:14,800
I guess it shows
that I haven't exercised in a while.

283
00:15:16,173 --> 00:15:18,100
- Shall we sit?
- Yeah.

284
00:15:29,233 --> 00:15:31,221
What's bothering you?

285
00:15:31,900 --> 00:15:34,233
Having trouble at work?

286
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:36,293
Not exactly.

287
00:15:38,733 --> 00:15:40,989
Actually,

288
00:15:41,533 --> 00:15:44,800
there's another reason
why I accepted the internship.

289
00:15:45,917 --> 00:15:47,100
What do you mean?

290
00:15:50,989 --> 00:15:53,300
I've secured the investment,

291
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:57,400
but I still can't access
the most important thing, the program.

292
00:15:57,833 --> 00:15:58,900
Do you really have to?

293
00:15:59,833 --> 00:16:01,100
You know my dream.

294
00:16:02,033 --> 00:16:03,600
I want to achieve it,

295
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:06,233
do what I love,

296
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:09,600
and be properly acknowledged by Mom.

297
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:11,500
Your mom already recognizes you.

298
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:14,100
You don't need to prove anything.

299
00:16:14,733 --> 00:16:15,833
Does she really?

300
00:16:17,079 --> 00:16:19,179
I think she still worries about me,

301
00:16:19,700 --> 00:16:21,133
so she wants me to settle...

302
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:23,500
for a big company job,
even if it's only an internship.

303
00:16:25,299 --> 00:16:28,700
Sounds like you have a lot bottled up.

304
00:16:30,033 --> 00:16:31,033
It's just that...

305
00:16:31,184 --> 00:16:34,700
I feel like I'm lacking.

306
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:36,033
That's not true.

307
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:39,300
You have more talent and passion
than anyone.

308
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:41,433
Believe in yourself.

309
00:16:44,016 --> 00:16:47,600
Talking to you makes me feel like
I'm actually a decent person.

310
00:16:48,106 --> 00:16:49,273
I feel more confident.

311
00:16:51,168 --> 00:16:53,600
So what's your worry, Dad?

312
00:16:56,144 --> 00:16:57,144
In front of your mom,

313
00:16:58,141 --> 00:16:59,541
I was a bit of a coward today.

314
00:17:00,157 --> 00:17:01,390
What do you mean?

315
00:17:02,122 --> 00:17:04,922
I acted like I was righteous,

316
00:17:05,933 --> 00:17:07,300
but it was the opposite.

317
00:17:08,467 --> 00:17:09,941
I didn't want her to find out,

318
00:17:10,831 --> 00:17:12,431
so I just got angry at her.

319
00:17:14,488 --> 00:17:16,349
It's all because I'm lacking.

320
00:17:16,749 --> 00:17:18,352
You're not lacking at all.

321
00:17:18,616 --> 00:17:20,700
Don't say that. It makes me sad.

322
00:17:22,633 --> 00:17:23,833
Both your brother and you...

323
00:17:24,333 --> 00:17:26,700
I know how hard you've worked.

324
00:17:27,633 --> 00:17:29,800
But in life,

325
00:17:30,996 --> 00:17:32,696
effort alone isn't enough.

326
00:17:35,243 --> 00:17:37,000
At times like this,

327
00:17:38,533 --> 00:17:40,500
I should be there to support you.

328
00:17:43,988 --> 00:17:44,988
Dad.

329
00:17:46,633 --> 00:17:48,400
Just being here,

330
00:17:49,064 --> 00:17:52,400
you're already our strength.

331
00:17:54,661 --> 00:17:55,733
Look at me.

332
00:17:55,733 --> 00:17:58,033
I grew up this well thanks to you.

333
00:18:00,539 --> 00:18:02,168
All right, let's go.

334
00:18:02,168 --> 00:18:03,468
Your mom must be waiting.

335
00:18:04,077 --> 00:18:05,900
I should go comfort her.

336
00:18:06,933 --> 00:18:08,600
Mom's lucky.

337
00:18:09,211 --> 00:18:11,000
To have such a kind,

338
00:18:11,233 --> 00:18:13,200
thoughtful husband like you.

339
00:18:14,833 --> 00:18:17,100
You're making me dizzy
with all that flattery.

340
00:18:18,433 --> 00:18:19,433
Let's go.

341
00:18:29,776 --> 00:18:31,633
What? Is that a fire?

342
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:32,900
Where?

343
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:36,800
It's hot!

344
00:18:38,861 --> 00:18:40,233
Seo Seung Wu!

345
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:42,500
What's going on?

346
00:18:43,133 --> 00:18:44,433
- Seung Ri, open the window.
- Okay.

347
00:18:44,968 --> 00:18:46,400
- I can't believe this.
- Wait.

348
00:18:47,243 --> 00:18:49,000
It's hot!

349
00:18:50,787 --> 00:18:52,555
What are you doing?

350
00:18:52,555 --> 00:18:53,900
I thought there was a fire.

351
00:18:54,155 --> 00:18:56,355
A fire?
I just burned something while cooking.

352
00:18:57,064 --> 00:18:59,833
This alarm is too sensitive.

353
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:01,200
My heart almost stopped.

354
00:19:04,233 --> 00:19:07,300
Father, Mother, I hope you slept well.

355
00:19:07,700 --> 00:19:10,800
I wished to prepare breakfast
for you myself,

356
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:12,233
but...

357
00:19:12,233 --> 00:19:13,600
What?

358
00:19:14,176 --> 00:19:16,760
You caused all this
trying to make breakfast?

359
00:19:16,760 --> 00:19:19,305
My heartfelt apologies.

360
00:19:19,633 --> 00:19:21,500
You've really outdone yourself.

361
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:23,100
Is it a historical webtoon this time?

362
00:19:25,064 --> 00:19:26,800
No, it's not that.

363
00:19:27,824 --> 00:19:30,400
Modern speech isn't enough...

364
00:19:30,805 --> 00:19:34,000
to express my deep respect
for our parents.

365
00:19:35,100 --> 00:19:37,700
You're laughing at this mess?

366
00:19:39,100 --> 00:19:41,000
What are we going to do with all this?

367
00:19:41,733 --> 00:19:43,304
Move aside.

368
00:19:43,304 --> 00:19:45,733
- Stop hitting me.
- You deserve it.

369
00:19:45,733 --> 00:19:47,200
You always make trouble.

370
00:19:48,233 --> 00:19:49,633
Wait. Fire!

371
00:19:53,063 --> 00:19:55,435
Seo Seung Wu, didn't you say
you were signing a contract?

372
00:19:55,829 --> 00:19:58,500
Yes,
even though I didn't pass the prelims,

373
00:19:59,496 --> 00:20:01,700
a producer recognized my genius.

374
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:04,300
You have to check everything properly.

375
00:20:04,443 --> 00:20:05,833
You know you can't just rush into things.

376
00:20:06,133 --> 00:20:07,400
Make sure the company is trustworthy...

377
00:20:07,512 --> 00:20:09,812
and go over the contract terms carefully.

378
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:11,700
No, send me the contract...

379
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:13,000
before you sign.

380
00:20:13,300 --> 00:20:15,233
There you go again, acting all superior.

381
00:20:15,733 --> 00:20:19,000
You might be a pro at your company,

382
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:22,100
but in the webtoon world,
you're just a nobody.

383
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:25,900
Fine, I'll trust you this time.

384
00:20:26,699 --> 00:20:27,848
I'm proud of you, my son.

385
00:20:28,677 --> 00:20:31,700
You really trashed the kitchen.

386
00:20:31,833 --> 00:20:32,787
Seung Ri, let's clean this up.

387
00:20:32,787 --> 00:20:34,219
Hurry up and clean this up.

388
00:20:34,341 --> 00:20:35,928
- Yes, Your Majesty.
- What were you even making?

389
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,933
What to do with all this mess and smell?

390
00:20:40,076 --> 00:20:41,076
Are you crazy?

391
00:20:41,379 --> 00:20:42,900
You're going to tell
the foundation you're turning it down?

392
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:44,033
Like I said,

393
00:20:44,416 --> 00:20:47,600
I can't do anything that goes against
my conscience and beliefs.

394
00:20:48,573 --> 00:20:50,600
No, about that money...

395
00:20:51,533 --> 00:20:53,437
Mother said she'd take care of it.

396
00:20:53,699 --> 00:20:56,900
What? You told Mom about the money?

397
00:20:58,059 --> 00:20:59,300
How could you?

398
00:20:59,300 --> 00:21:01,433
We're still waiting to hear
from other schools.

399
00:21:01,557 --> 00:21:03,677
But there's nothing else coming.

400
00:21:04,381 --> 00:21:07,360
Why don't you realize
this is your last chance?

401
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:08,433
Last chance?

402
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:11,600
No one knows how life will turn out.

403
00:21:11,837 --> 00:21:14,077
It's not something
you can predict so easily.

404
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:17,100
Please be realistic.

405
00:21:17,633 --> 00:21:18,833
You're the head of the family.

406
00:21:19,163 --> 00:21:21,500
You're responsible for Bit Na and me
for life!

407
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:24,533
Yes, I can't deny that.

408
00:21:24,851 --> 00:21:26,400
But how could you ask Mom to...

409
00:21:28,269 --> 00:21:30,133
She said she'd get the money,
whether it's a loan from Father's company,

410
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:32,100
or an advance on his severance.

411
00:21:32,776 --> 00:21:34,800
She said she'll find a way no matter what.

412
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:38,133
She told me not to worry and just wait!

413
00:21:38,236 --> 00:21:39,236
Wait.

414
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:41,600
A loan? Dad's severance pay?

415
00:21:43,300 --> 00:21:45,633
Ji Seon, what is wrong with you?

416
00:21:46,433 --> 00:21:47,433
(Dad)

417
00:21:50,128 --> 00:21:52,600
The person you're calling
is unavailable...

418
00:21:54,693 --> 00:21:57,291
Where are you going?
You need to take Bit Na to kindergarten.

419
00:21:57,347 --> 00:21:58,859
I just got home!

420
00:21:59,709 --> 00:22:02,300
- Bit Na.
- Mom, Dad, I hate you.

421
00:22:02,539 --> 00:22:05,233
You promised not to fight again.

422
00:22:07,005 --> 00:22:08,627
I'm sorry, Bit Na.

423
00:22:09,533 --> 00:22:10,933
But sometimes,

424
00:22:10,933 --> 00:22:13,233
adults have arguments
that children can't understand.

425
00:22:13,233 --> 00:22:15,333
But it's the same for kids too.

426
00:22:15,792 --> 00:22:19,700
Still, I wish you wouldn't fight.

427
00:22:20,488 --> 00:22:22,723
Okay, I'll try harder.

428
00:22:23,014 --> 00:22:24,014
Don't cry.

429
00:22:24,533 --> 00:22:25,633
Go with Mom today.

430
00:22:25,633 --> 00:22:27,000
I have something urgent to take care of.

431
00:22:27,333 --> 00:22:29,300
I'll pick you up this afternoon.

432
00:22:29,300 --> 00:22:30,300
I'm sorry.

433
00:22:30,936 --> 00:22:31,936
Eun Hyeong!

434
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:39,833
Don't cry. I'm sorry.

435
00:22:40,133 --> 00:22:42,100
(Kangsu Construction)

436
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:44,700
I'm really sorry.

437
00:22:45,347 --> 00:22:48,000
I lost control after drinking
and made a big mistake.

438
00:22:48,733 --> 00:22:49,733
No.

439
00:22:50,197 --> 00:22:54,200
Honestly, I don't remember anything.

440
00:22:55,504 --> 00:22:57,900
No, that's not it. What do I do?

441
00:22:58,797 --> 00:23:00,709
Are you going in or not?

442
00:23:00,851 --> 00:23:02,700
Team Manager...

443
00:23:09,043 --> 00:23:11,635
I remember everything now.

444
00:23:11,723 --> 00:23:12,723
What do you remember?

445
00:23:13,296 --> 00:23:15,433
I got drunk and...

446
00:23:16,123 --> 00:23:17,200
I'm really sorry.

447
00:23:19,833 --> 00:23:21,900
Then let's hear what you remember.

448
00:23:22,603 --> 00:23:25,500
What? Do I really have to say it myself?

449
00:23:25,997 --> 00:23:27,833
I need to know
if you remember correctly...

450
00:23:27,833 --> 00:23:30,300
to decide whether to accept your apology.

451
00:23:30,733 --> 00:23:31,800
That's cruel.

452
00:23:32,333 --> 00:23:34,280
Do I really have to say it out loud?

453
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:38,100
Can't we just let it slide?

454
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:39,900
Let it slide? Again?

455
00:23:40,233 --> 00:23:41,233
How?

456
00:23:41,533 --> 00:23:44,272
Did I do anything wrong to you?

457
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:48,100
Yes. You hired me
and then left me on my own.

458
00:23:48,300 --> 00:23:49,900
You tied a developer's hands...

459
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:52,100
and took away my purpose. And...

460
00:23:52,100 --> 00:23:53,100
What else?

461
00:23:54,221 --> 00:23:56,600
Other things too.

462
00:23:58,291 --> 00:24:00,600
You don't seem ready
to apologize properly.

463
00:24:00,733 --> 00:24:02,133
We'll talk later.

464
00:24:03,933 --> 00:24:05,300
Darn it.

465
00:24:05,300 --> 00:24:07,100
This is too much.

466
00:24:09,133 --> 00:24:10,776
What are you doing?

467
00:24:11,133 --> 00:24:12,616
As you know,

468
00:24:12,616 --> 00:24:14,733
I've been through a lot.

469
00:24:15,064 --> 00:24:16,233
I've been scammed...

470
00:24:16,233 --> 00:24:18,033
and even locked up once.

471
00:24:18,829 --> 00:24:20,200
Back in the day, my nickname was...

472
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:23,352
"Engineering Thug"
and "Engineering Psycho."

473
00:24:23,500 --> 00:24:25,168
"Psycho?"

474
00:24:25,347 --> 00:24:28,160
Yes, I'm usually calm,

475
00:24:28,533 --> 00:24:31,059
but when I snap, I go crazy.

476
00:24:31,696 --> 00:24:33,000
So?

477
00:24:33,571 --> 00:24:34,833
Today, wherever you go,

478
00:24:34,833 --> 00:24:36,500
I'm coming with you.

479
00:24:36,843 --> 00:24:38,100
Our family motto is...

480
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:40,200
"If you don't work, you don't eat."

481
00:24:40,397 --> 00:24:41,933
My goodness.

482
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:45,600
Good morning.

483
00:24:45,833 --> 00:24:47,000
Hello, Manager.

484
00:24:47,512 --> 00:24:49,000
I'm coming with you today!

485
00:24:53,712 --> 00:24:55,933
Ms. Cho Eun Ae,
can I see you for a moment?

486
00:24:55,933 --> 00:24:58,233
Yes? Team Manager!

487
00:24:58,233 --> 00:25:00,633
Please make five copies of this.

488
00:25:01,557 --> 00:25:03,100
Copies?

489
00:25:03,573 --> 00:25:05,000
Yes.

490
00:25:08,267 --> 00:25:10,233
Wait, what?

491
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:12,900
Executive Director Cho Seong Jun resigned?

492
00:25:12,900 --> 00:25:14,933
Yes, he left a year ago.

493
00:25:15,133 --> 00:25:16,300
No, that can't be.

494
00:25:16,600 --> 00:25:18,400
I'm sorry, but could you check again?

495
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:20,633
Yes, Director.

496
00:25:20,900 --> 00:25:23,333
I'm sorry,
I'll confirm and send it right away.

497
00:25:23,912 --> 00:25:25,400
Yes, sorry.

498
00:25:25,635 --> 00:25:26,900
What is going on?

499
00:25:27,569 --> 00:25:28,569
Why would Dad...

500
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:34,533
(Dad)

501
00:25:36,271 --> 00:25:37,271
Hey, Dad.

502
00:25:38,464 --> 00:25:39,900
Where are you?

503
00:25:40,233 --> 00:25:42,133
Where else? At the office.

504
00:25:43,136 --> 00:25:45,600
The meeting ran late,
so I couldn't take your call.

505
00:25:48,224 --> 00:25:49,300
Dad.

506
00:25:49,333 --> 00:25:51,700
I was going to talk to you.

507
00:25:52,469 --> 00:25:54,144
- Are you home?
- No.

508
00:25:54,144 --> 00:25:56,500
I'm at the Samho lobby to see you.

509
00:25:57,233 --> 00:25:59,600
What? Samho lobby?

510
00:26:01,160 --> 00:26:03,333
This is bad.

511
00:26:03,333 --> 00:26:06,933
I have another meeting now.

512
00:26:08,312 --> 00:26:10,100
No, it's fine.

513
00:26:11,533 --> 00:26:15,400
I have somewhere to be anyway.

514
00:26:15,433 --> 00:26:16,500
All right.

515
00:26:16,500 --> 00:26:18,400
Let's talk over dinner later.

516
00:26:18,805 --> 00:26:21,333
Yes, call me when you're free.

517
00:26:21,784 --> 00:26:24,133
- Okay.
- Bye.

518
00:26:48,669 --> 00:26:50,336
This is Joy, right?

519
00:26:50,336 --> 00:26:51,336
Can I take a look?

520
00:26:52,500 --> 00:26:54,033
You can't. The CPO said...

521
00:26:54,600 --> 00:26:56,900
it's to be kept strictly confidential,
especially from the competing team.

522
00:26:57,733 --> 00:26:58,800
Mr. Han Ji Hun!

523
00:26:59,333 --> 00:27:00,733
I have a meeting now.

524
00:27:01,633 --> 00:27:02,633
Wait...

525
00:27:06,617 --> 00:27:07,617
I can't take this anymore.

526
00:27:07,984 --> 00:27:10,069
How dare they mess with my Joy?

527
00:27:16,933 --> 00:27:18,100
(Not-So-Noble Ko Gyeol)

528
00:27:21,633 --> 00:27:22,633
Hey!

529
00:27:23,480 --> 00:27:24,633
Hello?

530
00:27:24,633 --> 00:27:26,500
Isn't that Ko Gyeol's phone?

531
00:27:26,500 --> 00:27:27,845
Yes,

532
00:27:28,347 --> 00:27:30,800
but he can't take a call right now.

533
00:27:31,173 --> 00:27:32,173
So please hang up.

534
00:27:32,333 --> 00:27:33,869
Wait!

535
00:27:33,869 --> 00:27:36,900
It's urgent.

536
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:38,533
Can you put him on?

537
00:27:39,173 --> 00:27:41,233
I said he can't.

538
00:27:41,872 --> 00:27:42,933
Excuse me.

539
00:27:43,379 --> 00:27:44,700
Where are you?

540
00:27:45,584 --> 00:27:46,833
I'm busy.

541
00:27:46,833 --> 00:27:49,237
We're on a mountain at Maeseok-ro...

542
00:27:50,833 --> 00:27:52,043
Look at this.

543
00:27:52,043 --> 00:27:53,200
- Wait.
- What?

544
00:27:54,200 --> 00:27:55,400
He's dead?

545
00:27:56,272 --> 00:27:58,837
Hello?

546
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:01,233
What?

547
00:28:01,233 --> 00:28:03,800
Team Manager is dead?

548
00:28:07,733 --> 00:28:10,500
(Our Happy Days)

549
00:28:10,633 --> 00:28:11,900
Where's Cho Eun Ae?

550
00:28:11,900 --> 00:28:13,933
